      "title": "People in Big Cities",
      "introHtml": "",
      "passageHtml": "<p class=\"rd-para\" data-para=\"1\">People in big cities often come from different places. <span class=\"rd-gap\" data-gap=\"1\"></span> People move to cities to get jobs or to find a better life, and many of them come from other countries. <strong>They</strong> often bring their culture, music and food with them. Visitors to London are often surprised to see so many Indian shops and restaurants, but over a million Indians live in the UK. <span class=\"rd-gap\" data-gap=\"2\"></span></p><p class=\"rd-para\" data-para=\"2\">Many European cities have large numbers of immigrants. There are Portuguese people in Paris and Turkish workers in Frankfurt. <strong>They</strong> are mostly there from the 1960s and 70s. But American cities have a very long tradition of new citizens from foreign countries. For example, San Francisco has more Chinese people than any city outside Asia. <span class=\"rd-gap\" data-gap=\"3\"></span> The city is famous for its Chinese restaurants. And New York, of course, is well known for its British and Irish citizens. <strong>The city</strong> has an Irish newspaper and its most important holiday is St Patrick's Day — the national day of Ireland. <span class=\"rd-gap\" data-gap=\"4\"></span> There are many Koreans from the 1980s and 90s in the US, especially in Los Angeles. In fact there is a large area in the center of Los Angeles that is called \"Korea town\".</p>",
